From:
David Raistrick keen(-at-)icantclick.org

EP/hypoid gear oil is generally only
really applicable for gearboxes with R&P - for some older gearboxes with
detached R&P the transmission itself is usually filled with straight mineral
oil (often subsituted today w/ motor oil).  FWIW.  There really are cases
where engine oil in the gearbox is the right thing.
